\ quickening: a polymorphic call site rewrites itself to the observed type's
\ handler after first execution; a type change demotes it back to the generic.
\ see-compiled names the current state of each cell.

\ === = on symbols quickens to (=.symbol) ===
: sym-eq :x :x = ;
sym-eq . cr
' sym-eq see-compiled

\ === @ on a symbol key quickens to (@.symbol) ===
: frame-read { :a 1 } :a @ ;
frame-read . cr
' frame-read see-compiled

\ === size on a len-carrying collection quickens to (size.len) ===
: len-of [ 1 2 3 ] size ;
len-of . cr
' len-of see-compiled

\ === a site whose types alternate demotes and stays correct ===
: alt = ;
:a :a alt . cr                \ 1
1 2 alt . cr                  \ 0
"x" "y" alt . cr              \ 0
:b :b alt . cr                \ 1
